  "response": "Here are some ways to build muscle at home:\n\n1. Bodyweight exercises\n- Push-ups\n- Pull-ups\n- Squats\n- Lunges\n- Planks\n- Dips\n\n2. Equipment options\n- Resistance bands\n- Dumbbells\n- Kettlebells\n- Weighted vest\n- Pull-up bar\n\n3. Workout strategies\n- Progressive overload (gradually increase repetitions/weight)\n- Compound movements targeting multiple muscle groups\n- High-intensity interval training (HIIT)\n\n4. Training tips\n- Aim for 3-4 workouts per week\n- Train each muscle group 2-3 times weekly\n- Rest between workouts\n- Focus on proper form\n\n5. Nutrition\n- Eat adequate protein (1.6-2.2g per kg of body weight)\n- Consume enough calories\n- Eat lean proteins, complex carbohydrates, healthy fats\n- Stay hydrated\n\n6. Recovery\n- Get enough sleep (7-9 hours)\n- Allow muscle recovery time\n- Stretch and warm up\n- Consider protein supplements\n\n7. Track progress\n- Take measurements\n- Take progress photos\n- Keep workout journal\n\nConsistency and patience are key to building muscle at home.",
